WEBVTT

00:02.252 --> 00:03.958
NARRATOR:
Previously on Smallville:

00:04.129 --> 00:08.714
Lois, you've had a lot of questions
about the Blur. It's me, I'm the Blur.

00:10.844 --> 00:14.803
-Lois Lane, will you marry me?
-Yes.

00:15.557 --> 00:17.047
I am Green Arrow.

00:17.267 --> 00:18.427
[REPORTERS CHATTERING]

00:18.601 --> 00:21.183
I think our audience would like
some answers.

00:21.354 --> 00:24.016
I lost someone.
She meant everything to me.

00:24.649 --> 00:26.185
| just stopped looking for you.

00:27.444 --> 00:29.605
Maybe that's what you wanted.
You could have called me—

00:29.779 --> 00:33.567
Yeah, I wanted to, but the fate helmet
warned me to stay away.

00:33.742 --> 00:36.859
-You sticking around for a while?
-Yeah.

00:37.037 --> 00:38.777
Good.

00:39.497 --> 00:41.533
There's something more
behind the darkness.

00:41.708 --> 00:44.199
Something hero-haters like Slade
don't know is affecting them.

00:44.377 --> 00:47.369
Before the facility exploded,
I saw something on Slade's skull.

00:47.547 --> 00:48.582
The Omega symbol.

00:48.965 --> 00:52.833
It was like it was branded there.
I think the Omega's a sign of corruption.

00:53.011 --> 00:55.297
A mark that the darkness
has taken over someone.

00:55.472 --> 00:57.588
This thing is an evil
spreading over the earth.

00:57.766 --> 00:59.848
lt preys upon the dark side
we already have.

01:00.018 --> 01:03.556
If we can't stop it, the darkness
will infect every person on this planet.

01:06.649 --> 01:07.855
GRAN NY:
Desaad?

01:08.026 --> 01:11.189
Our unholy trinity is complete.

01:11.362 --> 01:15.401
l bind their bodies,
Godfrey breaks their spirit...

01:15.617 --> 01:18.324
...and you, you clear their minds...

01:18.495 --> 01:20.656
...preparing the way for Lord Darkseid.

01:30.507 --> 01:35.126
Clark, I wanna plan this wedding as
much as I wanna jump off of a building.

01:35.303 --> 01:37.009
CLARK [OVER PHONE]:
You know I'd catch you.

01:37.180 --> 01:38.511
You're sweet.

01:38.681 --> 01:42.890
Now stop trying to dodge this bullet.
We've got a serious problem here.

01:43.061 --> 01:46.053
Tiny Lois has 37 possible guests
on her side.

01:46.231 --> 01:48.313
Do you know how many tiny Clark
has on his?

01:48.483 --> 01:50.189
Just tiny Martha?

01:50.360 --> 01:53.693
Tiny Martha is a sign
of a much larger problem.

01:53.863 --> 01:57.481
Sandwiching your super-friends into
the same place as my dad's battalion...

01:57.659 --> 01:58.990
...is a recipe for disaster.

01:59.160 --> 02:04.371
All it takes is one wrong person
recognizing the right face, and bam.

02:04.541 --> 02:06.372
We 7/ ﬁnd a way to make it work.

02:06.543 --> 02:09.410
That's easy for you to say
when you're calling from....

02:09.587 --> 02:12.499
[SIRENS WAILING OVER PHONE]

02:12.674 --> 02:13.789
Where the hell are you?

02:14.008 --> 02:15.134
[SIRENS WAILING]

02:15.301 --> 02:17.166
Just running some errands.

02:17.846 --> 02:20.804
Tell me you didn't hop across the pond
for a gallon of milk.

02:21.307 --> 02:23.389
What makes you think
I'd be in England?

02:27.689 --> 02:30.897
Oh, you know, because I'm kind of
staring at your face online.

02:58.970 --> 03:01.211
That better be some damn good milk,
Smallville.

03:01.848 --> 03:06.717
"Smallville." I must be in trouble.
How bad is it?

03:06.895 --> 03:08.681
[CROWD CHATTERING ON SCREEN]

03:08.855 --> 03:11.688
MAN 1: Look up in the sky.
MAN 2: Are you getting this?

03:11.858 --> 03:14.816
-Thinks he's the Blur.
WOMAN: Sure that is the Blur?

03:14.986 --> 03:17.728
MAN 2: Shouldn't he be across the pond?
MAN 3: The chap's here now.

03:17.906 --> 03:20.989
I didn't realize you were ready
for your close-up.

03:24.495 --> 03:27.282
And that is just the beginning.

03:32.420 --> 03:35.378
[REPORTER SPEAKING IN TURKISH
ON TV]

03:35.548 --> 03:36.788
[SIGHS]

03:36.966 --> 03:38.502
My Turkish is a little rusty...

03:38.676 --> 03:41.793
...but it seems someone managed
to pull off a super-save there...

03:41.971 --> 03:45.759
...and now Ankara's also wondering
who America's Blur hero is.

03:46.267 --> 03:49.725
Meanwhile, in Buenos Aires, they are
offering a national commendation...

03:49.896 --> 03:53.855
...to "El Salvador de Rojo y Azul," if he'd
stand still long enough to receive it.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.732
I won't bother with the Chinese
because I'd sound racist.

03:56.903 --> 04:01.112
I understand I got a little enthusiastic
after the VRA shut down, but....

04:01.282 --> 04:03.022
Lois...

04:03.201 --> 04:06.614
...the important thing is I made the save
and I didn't get caught.

04:06.788 --> 04:10.576
-At least, not really.
-Well, we were lucky this time.

04:14.963 --> 04:18.296
That was supposed to go out two days ago.
Why do you still have this?

04:18.466 --> 04:21.048
I realized we missed something
before I sent it there.

04:21.219 --> 04:23.301
l spellchecked it twice.

04:24.722 --> 04:28.135
You really don't see this? Clark.

04:33.481 --> 04:36.063
The whole world is starting to wonder
who the Blur is.

04:36.234 --> 04:40.193
You are so close to the story, you might
wind up smack-dab in the middle of it.

04:41.864 --> 04:45.197
I think it's high time
that we got you a new disguise.

05:40.423 --> 05:43.415
[BOSSHOUSE MUSIC'S "YOUR KISS"
PLAYING]

05:43.593 --> 05:46.585
[CROWD CHATTERING]

06:12.789 --> 06:15.451
You know, I'm supposed to be
meeting someone here.

06:15.625 --> 06:18.958
Oliver Queen, of all people.

06:19.629 --> 06:21.745
Even with the registration act
behind him...

06:21.923 --> 06:25.131
...the world still knows him
as the Green Arrow.

06:25.635 --> 06:27.421
He probably can't leave the house...

06:27.595 --> 06:29.631
...without wearing
some ridiculous disguise.

06:31.974 --> 06:35.216
Makes it pretty hard to live a normal life,
I'm guessing.

06:36.229 --> 06:40.347
You know, I heard he lost his company
to Lionel Luther.

06:42.777 --> 06:45.814
You wouldn't wanna have dinner
with me in his place, would you?

06:45.988 --> 06:48.946
Me? Well, what would your boyfriend
say about that?

06:49.117 --> 06:50.607
I hear he's a pretty tough guy.

06:50.785 --> 06:54.323
Well, I can't exactly call him
my boyfriend.

07:01.170 --> 07:03.957
I think Oliver Queen
would be an absolute fool...

07:04.132 --> 07:06.214
...to let someone like you get away.

07:06.843 --> 07:09.004
You're damn right.

07:11.097 --> 07:14.760
-Table for the Joneses?
-The real bitch of this whole thing...

07:14.934 --> 07:19.678
...Oliver Queen could waltz in here,
get a table just like that, no problem.

07:19.856 --> 07:22.313
But he wouldn't have the luxury
of eating in peace.

07:22.483 --> 07:25.975
Your brown-haired rendezvous here,
I can't even get on the list.

07:28.197 --> 07:31.030
Makes me wish
I was someone else entirely.

07:31.534 --> 07:34.116
Well, is it always so bad
being someone else?

07:34.287 --> 07:36.027
I'm quite enjoying myself.

07:37.665 --> 07:41.374
Last call for the Joneses.

07:42.170 --> 07:43.876
Over here.

07:45.339 --> 07:48.877
-What are you doing?
-We're the Joneses. the two of us.

07:49.552 --> 07:52.544
-We're the Joneses? We're the Joneses.
-Yeah.

07:54.265 --> 07:56.256
Right this way.

08:02.064 --> 08:04.396
-Here we are.
-Thank you.

08:07.028 --> 08:09.064
Enjoy.

08:10.198 --> 08:11.813
Look, we shouldn't be doing this.

08:11.991 --> 08:15.233
The universe gave a guy with a secret
and a girl with no identity...

08:15.411 --> 08:17.493
...the chance to enjoy an evening
in public.

08:19.499 --> 08:21.911
What's the worst that could happen?

08:23.294 --> 08:24.750
[GLASSES CLINK]

08:31.552 --> 08:33.258
Drink it in, handsome.

08:33.429 --> 08:35.761
Roll it around in your mouth
for a minute...

08:35.932 --> 08:37.342
...and tell me how you feel.

08:37.517 --> 08:41.260
| feel like I can't believe
that you did this to my jacket.

08:41.896 --> 08:45.388
Keep in mind it's a prototype.
It's not any worse than machine-gun ﬁre.

08:45.566 --> 08:47.943
The hood's not gonna stay up
during super-speed...

08:48.110 --> 08:50.601
...and I won't be able to see
through these glasses.

08:50.780 --> 08:54.398
Well, just use a bobby pin for the hood
when you're super-speeding...

08:54.575 --> 08:56.236
...and x-ray vision for the shades.

08:56.410 --> 08:59.322
Now stop giving me excuses...

08:59.747 --> 09:00.782
...and humor me.

09:00.957 --> 09:03.414
I don't wanna wear a mask.

09:03.584 --> 09:05.540
You are going global now...

09:05.711 --> 09:10.080
...which is awesome, frankly, but you
have spent more time in the shadows...

09:10.258 --> 09:12.123
...than you ever have in the spotlight.

09:12.301 --> 09:14.633
You're sticking your neck out
farther than before.

09:14.845 --> 09:16.972
I'm not gonna stop saving people.

09:18.474 --> 09:20.806
I can't believe you would think
I would want that.

09:20.977 --> 09:25.471
I know how important what you do is,
not just to you but to the whole world.

09:25.648 --> 09:29.140
Okay-- Do you remember who else
didn't wanna wear a mask?

09:29.360 --> 09:31.601
-Oliver.
-Oliver made his own choice.

09:31.779 --> 09:34.771
And whether you like it or not,
you've made one too.

09:35.324 --> 09:37.610
What is gonna happen
if people start thinking...

09:37.785 --> 09:40.071
...that Clark has what it takes
to save the day?

09:40.246 --> 09:42.328
Someone is gonna
put two and two together.

09:42.498 --> 09:44.159
Yeah, I appreciate your concern—

09:44.375 --> 09:47.333
And I don't understand
why you aren't more concerned.

09:47.503 --> 09:50.791
Oliver went from having
two identities to one...

09:50.965 --> 09:52.000
...to none.

09:54.176 --> 09:56.462
And I will stand by you
no matter what, okay?

09:58.639 --> 10:01.676
But is that really the life
you want for yourself?

10:04.103 --> 10:05.764
Yeah, I really should get to work.

10:05.938 --> 10:09.851
No. You do not get
to whoosh your way out of this one.

10:11.444 --> 10:13.105
Why don't I save you the trouble...

10:13.279 --> 10:15.986
...and I'll just super-speed off
all on my own, okay?

10:16.157 --> 10:17.522
Whoosh.

10:23.664 --> 10:25.825
CHLOE: That was delicious.
OLIVER: Mm-hm.

10:26.000 --> 10:29.288
-But-- Oh, my God, right?
-Oh.

10:30.880 --> 10:34.623
Phone call from your wife, Mr. Jones.

10:40.306 --> 10:42.513
Would you like my advice?

10:42.683 --> 10:47.143
You catch a cab, and you let him take
that limo of his back home. Alone.

10:50.775 --> 10:51.810
[CHLOE LAUGHS]

10:51.984 --> 10:53.940
I don't know.

10:55.529 --> 10:57.315
Hello, dear.

10:57.490 --> 11:01.233
I know this line isn't secure,
but you weren't answering your cell.

11:01.410 --> 11:05.619
I found them,
but I don't think I have much longer.

11:05.790 --> 11:06.825
Oh, my God.

11:06.999 --> 11:08.034
[MAN GRUNTING]

11:08.209 --> 11:09.494
Who is this?

11:12.088 --> 11:13.077
[OVER PHONE]
Hello?

11:13.255 --> 11:14.335
[GRUNTING]

11:14.507 --> 11:17.965
Is everything all right? Ma 'am?

11:19.595 --> 11:21.836
Hello, can you hear me?

11:23.265 --> 11:26.098
-What's happening?
-What do you mean, ma'am?

11:26.268 --> 11:29.601
-Hello?
-He found me.

11:29.772 --> 11:31.808
[SCREAMS]

11:31.982 --> 11:33.597
Hello? Who found you? Who is this?

11:33.776 --> 11:36.108
-Hello?
-Oliver.

11:38.531 --> 11:41.898
Who is this? Who found you?

11:42.076 --> 11:43.782
Hello?

11:44.912 --> 11:49.030
Don't worry, Mr. Jones,
you'll be joining her soon enough.

11:51.502 --> 11:52.787
-Oliver, what is it?
-Uh....

11:53.003 --> 11:57.872
I'm pretty sure Mrs. Jones, uh, just died.

11:59.719 --> 12:03.587
I think whoever the real Mr. Jones is,
is next on the list.

12:27.538 --> 12:29.870
-Can you trace it?
-The number the hostess had...

12:30.040 --> 12:33.203
...for the reservations matches
the number Mrs. Jones called from.

12:33.377 --> 12:35.754
If we wanna save Mr. Jones,
we need to ﬁnd him...

12:35.921 --> 12:38.128
...but we don't even know where to start.

12:40.259 --> 12:42.170
I think I might.

12:43.888 --> 12:46.595
Driver, we don't care
about the arrangements. We just—

12:46.766 --> 12:49.098
We need to get back to the Joneses'--
I mean, my place.

12:49.268 --> 12:50.553
[GUN COCKS]

12:50.728 --> 12:53.936
Mr. Jones, we've been looking for you.

13:00.696 --> 13:02.687
Easy. Yeah.

13:11.457 --> 13:12.867
[BOTH SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

13:13.542 --> 13:15.123
MAN 1:
We've already checked it out.

13:15.294 --> 13:17.080
MAN 2:
They're still waiting for detective--

13:17.254 --> 13:20.712
-Don't worry about it, Mr. Kent.
-Thank you.

13:21.717 --> 13:23.753
Mr. Kent.

13:23.928 --> 13:25.589
Clark Kent.

13:25.763 --> 13:29.301
Bert. Weren't you at that crime scene
the other day? The one with the, uh--

13:29.475 --> 13:30.715
-Robbery-homicide.
-Yeah.

13:30.893 --> 13:32.474
Yeah. Um, listen, Bert...

13:32.645 --> 13:35.762
...how is it that so many bodies
go for so long without being found?

13:35.940 --> 13:40.229
A DWP worker stumbled across them
in an abandoned tunnel beneath here.

13:40.402 --> 13:43.815
Looks like they were dumped
as recently as a few hours ago.

13:43.989 --> 13:45.945
Does Forensics have any leads?

13:46.116 --> 13:51.611
We're not gonna know anything more
until the coroner takes a closer look.

13:52.456 --> 13:55.948
Have you seen that viral clip
of the Blur from London?

13:56.126 --> 13:59.744
Because it was fuzzy,
but it looks so much like you.

13:59.922 --> 14:01.913
I don't spend much time
paying attention...

14:02.091 --> 14:05.629
...to what happens halfway
around the world. Thanks, Bert.

14:05.803 --> 14:07.088
[CH UCKLES]

14:07.263 --> 14:11.006
BERT: So, what do you think?
-Looks like a serial killer.

14:11.225 --> 14:15.468
"Looks like a serial killer."
Ha, ha. That is so you. Ha, ha.

14:15.646 --> 14:17.136
-ls it?
-You talk like a cop...

14:17.314 --> 14:20.772
...you walk like a ﬁreman, you beat us
to most of our own crime scenes.

14:20.943 --> 14:22.558
You might as well
put an S on your chest.

14:22.736 --> 14:24.601
[BERT YELPS THEN GRUNTS]

14:32.746 --> 14:34.452
You saved my life.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.866
Wait, how did you save my life?

14:39.044 --> 14:40.375
It was a, uh, adrenaline thing.

14:40.546 --> 14:43.128
Yeah, I'm a little bit bigger than you,
and, um....

14:43.299 --> 14:45.961
It probably has to do
with center of gravity.

14:47.177 --> 14:51.136
Don't be modest. You, sir...

14:51.348 --> 14:52.554
...are a hero.

14:53.976 --> 14:57.013
I'm sure I won't feel like one
in the morning.

15:20.169 --> 15:21.158
Excuse me.

15:21.337 --> 15:25.330
Forensics said it was all right I come
and follow up on the mass-grave story.

15:31.096 --> 15:32.131
[SIGHS]

15:32.306 --> 15:34.342
Sorry. I've just been so wrapped up
in all of this...

15:34.516 --> 15:37.007
...it was only a matter of time
before I made a mistake.

15:37.186 --> 15:39.177
-Clark Kent, Daily Planet.
-Blayne.

15:39.355 --> 15:42.518
Yeah, sorry about the mess,
I've been working faster than usual.

15:42.691 --> 15:45.933
Hell to pay if the boss ﬁnds out
I've been slacking off.

15:46.111 --> 15:49.023
I'll try not to take too much of your time.

15:53.869 --> 15:55.370
Any word on the cause of death?

15:55.537 --> 15:59.450
Yeah. She suffered a system-wide
hemorrhage starting with the heart.

15:59.625 --> 16:02.412
If they hadn't found the bodies
all grouped together...

16:02.586 --> 16:04.747
...l'd say natural causes, but....

16:05.381 --> 16:09.090
There's nothing natural about it.
Someone did this to these people.

16:10.260 --> 16:12.797
What kind of person
could do such a thing?

16:12.972 --> 16:19.263
My guess is someone who's given in
to his or her darkest urges.

16:19.436 --> 16:24.055
From the number of bodies, probably
someone who really enjoys it too.

16:47.089 --> 16:48.920
Did I miss something?

16:49.091 --> 16:51.798
Did the rest of the bodies have this?

16:55.764 --> 16:59.097
I'll be damned. Nice eye.

16:59.268 --> 17:01.429
If so, there might be a connection
we can make between—

17:01.603 --> 17:04.094
Nah. I'm the guilty one.

17:05.524 --> 17:07.765
Had a pen pop earlier
while I was taking notes.

17:09.653 --> 17:12.611
Had you going for a second, huh?
Sorry.

17:14.033 --> 17:17.525
-Thank you for your time, Blayne.
-Yeah.

17:36.430 --> 17:39.388
When I said I wanted to spoon earlier,
this isn't really what I had in mind.

17:39.558 --> 17:40.593
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

17:40.768 --> 17:44.511
We're lying alone together in the dark.
I think that counts for something.

17:44.688 --> 17:48.727
You're probably right. This is the most
romantic of my recent kidnappings.

17:48.942 --> 17:51.809
Hell of a way
to spend an anniversary, right?

17:54.448 --> 17:55.483
Oh, gee, you forgot.

17:55.657 --> 18:00.993
No. No. No, I did not forget that
it's been a year since we started doing....

18:01.163 --> 18:02.869
Whatever it is that we're doing.

18:03.040 --> 18:05.156
Whatever it is that we're-- Wow.

18:05.334 --> 18:09.077
You weren't joking at the restaurant.
You don't know what to call me.

18:09.254 --> 18:10.664
Not in so many words.

18:10.839 --> 18:12.170
-Okay.
-Oliver, come on.

18:12.341 --> 18:14.673
We spend every waking moment
together, right?

18:14.843 --> 18:17.710
We've said our "I love yous"
how many times? Several.

18:17.888 --> 18:19.219
What do you call that?

18:21.266 --> 18:22.722
CHLOE:
Ow.

18:22.893 --> 18:26.010
-Can we talk about this later?
-Yeah, no, I'd love to do that...

18:26.188 --> 18:27.598
...if there is a later.

18:27.773 --> 18:29.183
You're so dramatic.

18:29.358 --> 18:30.393
[CAR DOORS OPEN THEN CLOSE]

18:33.070 --> 18:34.230
SIMON:
On your feet.

18:34.404 --> 18:36.861
You got some explaining to do.

18:50.295 --> 18:53.162
All right, all right, enough of this.
What'd you guys do with Mrs. Jones?

18:53.340 --> 18:54.671
Huh? Huh?

18:55.509 --> 18:57.124
We were about to ask the same thing.

18:57.302 --> 18:59.714
What? Am I the only one
who's confused here?

18:59.888 --> 19:02.550
We know you aren't the Joneses.
Who are you?

19:04.143 --> 19:08.557
Yeah, he's right.
We should, uh, introduce ourselves.

19:08.772 --> 19:11.605
[ALL GRUNTING]

19:47.769 --> 19:51.432
BOTH:
Oh. I love you.

19:51.899 --> 19:53.105
OLIVER:
Mm.

20:01.783 --> 20:03.569
What the hell is that?

20:11.501 --> 20:13.662
Mr. and Mrs. Jones
weren't married at all.

20:15.297 --> 20:17.083
They were on a stakeout. FBI.

20:17.299 --> 20:20.086
I know. We just wiped the ﬂoor
with their backup.

20:20.302 --> 20:22.293
They probably
couldn't break their cover...

20:22.471 --> 20:25.804
...until they found out how we were
connected to the missing agents.

20:28.143 --> 20:30.759
From what Mrs. Jones said,
their cover was blown...

20:30.938 --> 20:33.475
...which means Mr. Jones
is probably in grave danger.

20:37.110 --> 20:39.647
CHLOE:
I think that's a deﬁnite.

20:41.823 --> 20:44.314
What makes you say that?

20:44.868 --> 20:46.028
Call it a hunch.

20:49.331 --> 20:51.242
The darkness.

21:03.011 --> 21:06.003
-No one's answering out front.
-And the last thing we want...

21:06.181 --> 21:09.469
...is for a billionaire superhero
ex-fugitive to get caught...

21:09.643 --> 21:11.679
...kicking in the front door
of a sex club.

21:11.853 --> 21:14.936
Yeah, not today, anyway.
We sure this is the right place?

21:15.107 --> 21:16.722
It's owned by a guy named Desaad.

21:16.900 --> 21:19.277
The feds have been keeping
an eye on it for weeks.

21:19.444 --> 21:22.402
Some guy from the bureau came here
for a bit of relaxation...

21:22.572 --> 21:24.312
...and at his checkup the next week--

21:24.491 --> 21:28.154
-There was an Omega on his skull.
-Yeah. Turns out he wasn't the only one.

21:28.370 --> 21:31.908
Every one of those x-rays belongs to
someone who was a visitor at this club.

21:35.252 --> 21:36.913
The Joneses may have gotten made...

21:37.087 --> 21:40.204
...but they had no idea
what they were getting themselves into.

21:40.590 --> 21:42.717
-Hey.
-Right. Which is why it's ourjob...

21:42.884 --> 21:46.342
-...to get Mr. Jones out of it.
-Don't leave Goldilocks out in the cold.

21:46.513 --> 21:48.754
If the darkness has anything
to do with this...

21:48.932 --> 21:51.969
...the last thing I want
is for you to get caught in the crossﬁre.

21:57.941 --> 21:58.976
[GUN COCKS]

21:59.151 --> 22:03.645
MAN: Hands where I can see them.
-Come on. Again?

22:05.032 --> 22:06.613
Mr. Jones.

22:06.783 --> 22:08.648
-Or Agent--?
-Vactor.

22:08.827 --> 22:12.615
Whoever you are, you're under arrest
for impeding a federal investigation.

22:12.789 --> 22:16.077
Listen— You have no idea
what you're dealing with here.

22:16.251 --> 22:18.958
No, what you don't understand is....

22:21.590 --> 22:22.875
[VACTOR GRUNTS]

22:25.093 --> 22:26.173
Desaad.

22:26.345 --> 22:28.927
He really didn't have a clue.

22:31.266 --> 22:33.348
But not you.

22:33.560 --> 22:35.676
You know all about me.

22:39.107 --> 22:40.972
[CHLOE GRUNTING]

22:44.488 --> 22:48.197
I think it's only fair
if I get to know you a little better.

22:53.455 --> 22:55.411
I am getting really tired of excuses here.

22:55.582 --> 22:59.916
-Miss Lane, I'm working as--
-Risotto cheese bites?

23:00.087 --> 23:02.999
Should we just serve up
hot charcoal too?

23:03.173 --> 23:04.333
What do you have for me?

23:04.508 --> 23:06.715
These just came in from Bert
in Forensics.

23:06.885 --> 23:09.501
He says you're lucky to be engaged
to such a super guy.

23:09.679 --> 23:12.091
-Ahh. Does he, now?
-Mm-hm.

23:12.265 --> 23:14.096
Is there anything else you need?

23:15.102 --> 23:18.094
How would you feel about negotiating
a deal across town for me?

23:19.856 --> 23:20.891
Uh....

23:21.066 --> 23:23.307
-This is a bakery.
-Yes, it is.

23:23.485 --> 23:27.353
And why don't you get me a good rate
on vanilla-bean frosting? Pretty please?

23:27.531 --> 23:29.021
Okay.

23:29.199 --> 23:31.986
Oh. Mr. Kent, I'm sorry.

23:32.994 --> 23:35.485
I guess you heard
what happened at the crime scene.

23:35.664 --> 23:37.655
So if there's anything you have to say....

23:37.833 --> 23:39.073
Not me. Nope.

23:39.251 --> 23:41.708
I am a positive, supportive,
independent woman...

23:42.295 --> 23:44.786
...and I just wanna know
what happened at the morgue.

23:45.006 --> 23:49.295
The coroner couldn't make a connection
between the bodies. It's a dead end.

23:53.098 --> 23:54.304
Dead end? Seriously?

23:54.850 --> 23:57.011
What do you call it
when you have zero leads?

23:57.185 --> 23:59.221
A lie.

24:01.064 --> 24:03.521
Here, take a look
at these crime-scene photos.

24:06.736 --> 24:10.069
There's a stamp on each of the
victims' hands. I only saw a few dots.

24:10.240 --> 24:13.698
Must have been some relief pattern.
It matches the stamp right there.

24:20.041 --> 24:21.656
That's a fraction of a centimeter.

24:21.835 --> 24:24.542
-How would you be able to see that?
-Micro-vision.

24:25.213 --> 24:26.623
Micro-vision?

24:27.632 --> 24:29.793
It's my power,
I can call it whatever I want.

24:32.345 --> 24:34.961
The coroner wasn't examining
those bodies, Lois.

24:35.140 --> 24:36.630
He was covering his tracks.

24:45.108 --> 24:48.600
It's another dead end. No one at the morgue
recognized the name Blayne.

24:48.778 --> 24:51.155
The stamp was made for
an anonymous private buyer.

24:51.323 --> 24:53.029
Chloe?

24:53.200 --> 24:54.815
Lois, let me call you back.

24:54.993 --> 24:57.609
-Oliver, what happened?
-That's what happened.

25:01.458 --> 25:04.621
Lois and I are trying to ﬁnd a serial killer
who uses that stamp.

25:05.086 --> 25:07.919
Serial killer. This just keeps getting
better and better.

25:08.089 --> 25:10.341
There's a photo in there
of a guy named Desaad.

25:10.509 --> 25:13.672
He owns a nightclub he's using
to put Omegas on people's heads.

25:16.348 --> 25:19.966
He's an agent of the darkness,
just like Godfrey.

25:21.269 --> 25:23.931
There were no Omega symbols
on the bodies in the morgue.

25:24.231 --> 25:26.472
He must be killing the people
he can't convert.

25:26.650 --> 25:28.811
And now he's got Chloe.

25:29.110 --> 25:32.398
Which means if we can't ﬁnd her,
she's either damned or dead.

25:33.156 --> 25:36.068
The business, it's registered
to an address on 4th Street.

25:36.243 --> 25:37.653
Maybe that's where they took her.

25:37.827 --> 25:39.328
-Terriﬁc.
-Wait a sec.

25:39.829 --> 25:42.787
-What are you doing?
-You're upset and in no condition to go.

25:42.958 --> 25:47.998
-And you're in a better condition?
-I don't have a choice. Now, stay put.

25:50.215 --> 25:52.001
Like hell.

25:57.639 --> 25:58.754
[GRUNTS]

26:11.069 --> 26:14.061
[WHIMPERING]

26:26.501 --> 26:28.492
Clark.

26:28.670 --> 26:30.456
Chloe.

26:32.090 --> 26:33.170
[CLARK GRUNTS]

26:35.468 --> 26:38.596
-I thought I lost you.
-I thought I lost me too.

26:38.763 --> 26:41.049
I can't go through that again.

26:43.518 --> 26:45.474
Chloe...

26:45.854 --> 26:47.560
...you know when something happens...

26:47.731 --> 26:50.689
...and suddenly you're afraid
that you can never go back?

26:50.859 --> 26:53.441
Where you get these ﬂashes
going through your mind...

26:53.612 --> 26:55.477
...ﬁashes that you never expected?

26:56.281 --> 26:58.146
Flashes of you and I.

26:59.409 --> 27:01.525
As in...?

27:03.079 --> 27:04.865
What if we missed our chance?

27:07.459 --> 27:09.040
What are you talking about?

27:09.919 --> 27:10.999
One kiss.

27:12.380 --> 27:14.245
Come on. We never have to tell anyone.

27:14.716 --> 27:17.207
After all those years,
don't you wanna know?

27:20.805 --> 27:22.511
No.

27:24.100 --> 27:25.715
No.

27:30.482 --> 27:33.098
OLIVER: Chloe.
-Oliver.

27:33.276 --> 27:35.312
Thank God.

27:36.029 --> 27:38.862
-Did I just see--?
-Ollie, something's wrong with Clark.

27:39.032 --> 27:41.819
Yeah, I know.
That's why we have to get out of here.

27:43.244 --> 27:47.203
Let me run away with you this time.
No more disguises, no more darkness.

27:48.333 --> 27:50.574
I would never ask you to do that.

27:50.752 --> 27:52.617
Why would you ever think
that I would—?

27:52.796 --> 27:54.752
It's okay.

27:55.632 --> 27:58.590
We don't have to try so hard
to be heroes. We're just human.

27:58.760 --> 28:02.127
There's plenty enough people here
to ﬁght the good ﬁght without us.

28:02.305 --> 28:04.091
Come on, Chloe. We can be together.

28:06.101 --> 28:08.262
Just take my hand.

28:08.770 --> 28:10.135
Come on.

28:14.651 --> 28:16.312
Come on.

28:18.446 --> 28:20.357
Who are you?

28:21.282 --> 28:23.147
Wait a minute, what is this?

28:25.328 --> 28:27.660
This isn't happening.

28:28.748 --> 28:30.579
Chloe.

28:32.627 --> 28:34.458
You aren't real, either.

28:35.130 --> 28:36.666
Real enough for you to wonder...

28:36.840 --> 28:40.458
...if you will ever feel the happiness
that Clark and I do.

28:40.844 --> 28:42.755
You envy what we have.

28:43.596 --> 28:47.054
No. I have only ever been happy
for Lois and Clark.

28:47.225 --> 28:48.761
Wait.

28:49.310 --> 28:51.016
Envy.

28:51.771 --> 28:53.807
Leaving with Ollie would be sloth.

28:53.982 --> 28:58.225
And Clark's kiss is lust.

28:59.654 --> 29:01.565
You're trying to tempt me.

29:03.158 --> 29:04.489
Bravo.

29:05.034 --> 29:08.071
But knowing that
doesn't change how you feel.

29:08.621 --> 29:11.112
You just have to admit it.

29:11.291 --> 29:15.785
You gave up everything that l have,
and do you want it back?

29:17.881 --> 29:19.712
Never.

29:20.008 --> 29:21.293
Get out of my head.

29:24.637 --> 29:26.593
It's the heart, actually.

29:26.765 --> 29:29.472
The window to the soul.

29:29.642 --> 29:35.228
Both mankind's greatest asset
and his weakness.

29:35.732 --> 29:39.020
You're gonna put me through
the seven-deadly-sins house of horror...

29:39.194 --> 29:41.856
...to try and convert me
into one of your dark denizens?

29:42.030 --> 29:43.861
A little on the nose, don't you think?

29:44.032 --> 29:50.119
Oh, you might balk, but it's worked
for me for a very long time.

29:51.748 --> 29:54.785
Most of you are quite easy to turn...

29:55.960 --> 29:59.623
...but others require a little persuading.

29:59.798 --> 30:01.254
[CHLOE GRUNTS]

30:01.925 --> 30:05.543
The visions tend to cut
to the heart of the matter.

30:05.804 --> 30:09.262
Sin is a liability I exploit.

30:09.432 --> 30:12.299
You are more vulnerable than you think.

30:14.896 --> 30:16.386
You know what I am.

30:17.398 --> 30:20.185
You know what I'm capable of.

30:23.321 --> 30:24.356
Kill me.

30:25.198 --> 30:28.440
Your friends will all die if you don't.

30:33.248 --> 30:36.160
Trying to get me on wrath now, huh?

30:36.334 --> 30:38.199
Nice try...

30:38.378 --> 30:40.334
...but I'm stronger than that.

30:44.592 --> 30:47.334
We are stronger than that, aren't we?

30:49.138 --> 30:51.971
We can resist any temptation,
but what if we're doing it...

30:52.141 --> 30:55.269
...to save our own souls
when we could be saving the world?

30:55.436 --> 30:57.768
I will not take a life, period.

30:57.939 --> 31:01.056
Good girl. Stay strong.

31:01.234 --> 31:03.316
Beat him at his own game.

31:03.611 --> 31:06.023
Feels good, doesn't it?

31:06.906 --> 31:10.444
To be better than all of those
that fell before him.

31:10.618 --> 31:11.698
Pride.

31:11.870 --> 31:18.241
That's our hubris, our fatal ﬂaw.
Our control issues...

31:18.543 --> 31:22.286
...our grossly disproportionate
sense of independence.

31:22.463 --> 31:24.044
Too proud to ask for help.

31:25.216 --> 31:27.127
That's why we vanished
without a trace.

31:27.302 --> 31:28.792
Shut up.

31:28.970 --> 31:31.962
CHLOE: Too proud to face the fact
that the world moved on without us.

31:32.140 --> 31:33.300
I said, enough!

31:33.474 --> 31:37.092
All that effort you spent freeing yourself
from your old identity...

31:37.270 --> 31:40.512
...to suddenly give everything over
for something lesser...

31:40.690 --> 31:42.146
...for a relationship.

31:50.867 --> 31:52.323
Go to hell.

31:52.493 --> 31:55.235
No. It'll be here soon enough.

31:56.205 --> 31:57.240
Sadly...

31:57.916 --> 32:01.283
...you've grown just as useless
as that knife.

32:01.753 --> 32:08.249
Tell me, Chloe, when's the last time
you had a nice, hard cry?

32:12.680 --> 32:15.547
I was wondering when we'd meet again.

32:16.351 --> 32:18.512
What exactly are you, Desaad?

32:18.728 --> 32:20.719
A prophet.

32:20.897 --> 32:25.231
A servant, loyal to a far greater power.

32:28.446 --> 32:32.030
-To darkness.
-To Darkseid.

32:33.326 --> 32:38.616
When he last laid eyes upon you,
you wore your sin openly.

32:38.998 --> 32:41.205
You're much more self-assured now.

32:41.376 --> 32:45.289
More love in your heart
than when you faced Godfrey.

32:45.505 --> 32:49.248
Stronger than when you faced Granny,
as well.

32:50.426 --> 32:53.793
Sadly, incorruptible.

32:54.222 --> 32:58.431
They, much like I, have been preparing
for something...

32:58.810 --> 33:01.096
-...amazing.
-And that's why the three of you...

33:01.270 --> 33:03.886
...have been burning your symbols
into innocent people.

33:04.065 --> 33:07.398
You act as though
the marks weren't there to begin with.

33:08.027 --> 33:10.018
But I wouldn't wanna
ruin the surprise.

33:17.036 --> 33:18.071
[GRUNTS]

33:22.125 --> 33:24.741
[THUNDER CRASHING]

33:27.588 --> 33:28.794
[BEEPS]

33:32.427 --> 33:35.260
Good things come to those who wait.

33:35.430 --> 33:36.636
[OLIVER GRUNTS]

33:36.806 --> 33:38.171
Where the hell is she, huh?!

33:38.766 --> 33:40.973
She screamed for you as she died.

33:44.772 --> 33:46.353
[OLIVER GRUNTING]

33:47.984 --> 33:50.100
[GRUNTING]

33:53.573 --> 33:54.608
[GRUNTS]

33:56.075 --> 33:58.862
Took me a while to ﬁgure out
Chloe's weakness.

33:59.078 --> 34:02.366
But not you.
No, your sin is ripe for the picking.

34:11.591 --> 34:13.047
-Chloe's alive.
-He killed her.

34:13.217 --> 34:14.377
I saved her.

34:17.096 --> 34:18.381
She's safe.

34:24.062 --> 34:27.520
-Oliver.
-l'm ﬁne.

34:44.499 --> 34:49.118
The guy who left his calling card across
the globe suddenly doesn't want credit?

34:49.712 --> 34:53.125
I asked for my name to be taken off.
You're right, Lois...

34:53.299 --> 34:57.212
...l've been drawing too much attention
to myself. I've been doing this all wrong.

34:57.386 --> 35:00.344
I'm sorry. I should have known
the pressure you were under...

35:00.515 --> 35:03.678
...and not made things
more difﬁcult for you.

35:04.227 --> 35:06.684
And I should be wearing a mask.

35:08.481 --> 35:12.349
Unfortunately, I've lived my entire life
up until this point without needing one.

35:12.527 --> 35:15.314
That's why I've been so reluctant.

35:15.488 --> 35:17.649
This is the face of the man
my parents raised.

35:17.824 --> 35:20.531
It's the face of the man that you love.

35:21.410 --> 35:24.538
I don't wanna deny who I am
when I'm doing what I was born to do.

35:24.705 --> 35:27.617
Then why bother with the jacket, Clark?
The symbols?

35:28.543 --> 35:32.331
When I'm out there in the red and blue
saving people, that's who I really am.

35:32.505 --> 35:33.711
This is gonna sound weird...

35:33.881 --> 35:36.668
...but it's not what I'm called
that should deﬁne who I am.

35:36.843 --> 35:40.051
It's who I am
that should deﬁne what I'm called.

35:40.888 --> 35:43.880
Clark Kent, it's just a name.

35:44.392 --> 35:46.257
It's just a word.

35:47.145 --> 35:49.557
I am the Blur, and I always have been.

35:51.691 --> 35:57.061
That is a pretty amazing breakthrough.
And I'm really happy to hear it...

35:57.238 --> 36:01.732
...but if you wanna keep doing things
like, I don't know, working here...

36:01.909 --> 36:05.367
...and marrying moi, I don't see how
we're gonna make this work.

36:05.538 --> 36:06.948
By doing what we talked about.

36:07.165 --> 36:09.372
The answer's been staring me
right in the face.

36:09.542 --> 36:11.783
The Blur can't whip out
a new costume at work.

36:11.961 --> 36:15.419
The Blur is not the disguise, Lois.

36:15.590 --> 36:17.546
Clark Kent will be the mask.

36:20.052 --> 36:23.795
Okay. But the only way that the glasses
are ever going to work—

36:23.973 --> 36:26.259
If I adjust my behavior when I use them?
I know.

36:26.434 --> 36:29.551
The world needs to believe
Clark Kent is too normal to ever be—

36:29.729 --> 36:32.311
-Super.
-Even though we've silenced Godfrey...

36:32.481 --> 36:36.065
...shut down Granny's orphanage and
buried Desaad underneath Belle Reve...

36:36.235 --> 36:38.442
...it's not the last time
we've seen Darkseid.

36:40.948 --> 36:42.904
But I'll be ready...

36:43.618 --> 36:46.325
...hiding in plain sight.

36:47.955 --> 36:50.412
So you're willing to dial back
the hometown hero...

36:50.583 --> 36:52.323
...and crank up the average Joe?

36:52.501 --> 36:55.834
If that's what it takes
to be the hero the people need...

36:56.214 --> 36:58.921
...yes, Miss Lane, I am.

37:00.426 --> 37:05.637
Did you know that average ﬁancés let
their ladies take them to cake tastings?

37:07.475 --> 37:09.636
You have to act
like you're miserable, though.

37:09.810 --> 37:11.971
That shouldn't be a problem.

37:16.150 --> 37:19.142
You really need to watch
where you're going, buddy.

37:19.320 --> 37:20.776
Jeff.

37:26.118 --> 37:28.325
I am so sorry, Mr. Kent.

37:30.164 --> 37:33.281
You know, Jeff, um, it's my fault.

37:33.459 --> 37:35.996
I'll try to be more careful next time.

37:37.004 --> 37:39.256
You, uh.... Ahem.

37:40.549 --> 37:43.006
You probably should.

37:50.476 --> 37:52.762
Good job, Mr. Kent.

38:10.871 --> 38:12.281
OLIVER:
You all right?

38:15.209 --> 38:19.418
I escaped the villain of the piece
with nary a mark on my bones.

38:19.797 --> 38:20.877
I would expect nothing less.

38:21.048 --> 38:22.629
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

38:24.343 --> 38:26.834
You know, the whole
woman-who-doesn't-exist thing...

38:27.013 --> 38:29.550
...gets less mysterious
when yearbooks come into play.

38:30.891 --> 38:33.268
Yeah, they're kind of a breadcrumb.

38:33.436 --> 38:35.848
Meaning what?

38:37.231 --> 38:39.893
You feeling lost, Chloe?

38:40.067 --> 38:42.729
I have been so many things
over the years.

38:42.903 --> 38:46.896
Doe-eyed sleuth, intrepid reporter,
Watchtower--

38:47.074 --> 38:49.690
-Business-suited cyber-savior.
-It worked, right?

38:49.869 --> 38:51.279
Yeah.

38:51.454 --> 38:57.745
I've always wound up deﬁning myself
by some group or cause or other person.

38:57.918 --> 38:59.169
Um....

38:59.337 --> 39:01.248
I haven't felt like Chloe since—

39:01.422 --> 39:05.210
Well, Chloe 1.0, anyway, since....

39:07.762 --> 39:09.878
Well, her.

39:10.431 --> 39:13.969
And then I erased it all.
I gave it all away.

39:14.977 --> 39:19.095
I think that's why I've been struggling
to deﬁne myself against you.

39:20.566 --> 39:25.731
I'm afraid I'm gonna lose
the last little bit of me that I have left.

39:26.364 --> 39:28.650
No matter what happens...

39:29.408 --> 39:31.148
...I know who you are.

39:33.788 --> 39:35.494
I know.

39:35.873 --> 39:40.412
And that's why I have never questioned
the love I feel for you.

39:50.388 --> 39:52.379
So, what do we do now?

39:54.767 --> 39:58.385
Hey. Chloe, listen.

39:58.896 --> 40:01.478
I know how hard you worked
to disappear...

40:01.649 --> 40:04.516
...but I'm gonna be in the spotlight
for the rest of my life.

40:05.319 --> 40:08.106
I was kidding myself with this
trying-to-be-normal thing.

40:09.281 --> 40:11.488
I thought I was, um...

40:12.159 --> 40:15.322
...giving up my identity by coming out...

40:16.705 --> 40:19.037
...but all I did was change it.

40:20.709 --> 40:22.870
Because I am who I am.

40:23.045 --> 40:25.331
It's time I stopped hiding from that.

40:25.965 --> 40:28.206
I made this bed...

40:29.343 --> 40:31.208
...and now I have to sleep in it.

40:32.847 --> 40:35.509
Well, you don't have to do it alone.

40:38.561 --> 40:39.971
Really?

40:42.690 --> 40:46.148
So I got a question for you.
When people see this adorable blond...

40:46.318 --> 40:50.061
...and you are on
this adorable blond's arm...

40:52.032 --> 40:53.363
...what do they call you?

40:55.161 --> 40:59.825
Let's start with girlfriend
and go from there?

41:01.041 --> 41:03.498
Okay.
"Girlfriend" sounds kind of high school.

41:03.669 --> 41:05.660
-Shut up. I'm serious.
-I know.

41:14.513 --> 41:16.970
-Let's get out of here.
-Okay.

41:21.979 --> 41:23.014
You coming?

41:23.189 --> 41:25.771
I'll be right down.
I have to turn off some equipment.

41:25.983 --> 41:28.474
You know who pays the power bill
around here, right?

42:17.993 --> 42:19.984
[English - US - SDH]
